Nathaniel Porter and Sebastian Karcher librarians from Virginia Tech and Syracuse University have published an article on their workshops using QualCoder and Taguette.
They describe how they set their workshops up, and how much teaching was given over to learning software and over to learning about qualitative analysis.

Porter, Nathaniel D., and Sebastian Karcher. 2026. “Building Open Qualitative Science with Open Curriculum.” 
Journal of eScience Librarianship 15 (1): e1172. [https://doi.org/10.7191/jeslib.1172](https://doi.org/10.7191/jeslib.1172)
